# Avoid These Mistakes — Scalable & Adaptive Anti-Patterns

> **Purpose:** Mandatory pre-coding checklist and design gate. Before writing or modifying ANY code, run **Section 0** (context discovery), apply **Section 1** domain priorities when detected, then enforce **Sections 2–12** (universal rules). Industry-specific rules never replace universal ones — they **stack and elevate** critical invariants.

**Related rules (do not contradict):** `no-hardcoded-env-vars` (config singleton), `test-driven-development`, `systems-thinking`, `safe-git-push`.

---

## 0. MANDATORY AGENT WORKFLOW (EVERY TASK)

Before implementation, explicitly complete this gate in your reasoning or task brief:

### 0.1 Context discovery (automated)

Scan the **current task scope** (files touched, open files, user request) and **project footprint**:

| Signal source | What to look for |
|---|---|
| Dependencies | `package.json`, `pyproject.toml`, `requirements.txt`, `go.mod`, `Cargo.toml`, `pom.xml` |
| Layout | `services/`, `apps/`, `packages/`, `contracts/`, `workers/`, `migrations/` |
| Data layer | Spanner, Postgres, MySQL, MongoDB, Redis, Neo4j, BigQuery, Snowflake, DynamoDB, vector DB clients |
| Messaging | Kafka, RabbitMQ, Pub/Sub, SQS, Celery, Temporal, Airflow |
| AI/ML | OpenAI, Anthropic, Vertex, LangChain, vector stores, embedding pipelines |
| Auth/compliance | OAuth, SAML, RBAC libs, HIPAA/FHIR, PCI, SOC2 mentions in docs |
| Runtime | FastAPI, Express, Django, Spring, Lambda, Cloud Run, K8s manifests |

### 0.2 Declare active domain profile(s)

- Match **one or more** profiles from **Section 1** (hybrid systems are common).
- If **no profile matches**, use **PROFILE Z (General Application)** only.
- State in output: `Active profiles: [A, C]` + **top 3 invariants** per profile + **which anti-patterns are P0** for this task.

### 0.3 Calibrate depth to scope

| Scope | Minimum enforcement |
|---|---|
| Trivial (typo, comment) | Universal checklist §12 — quick pass |
| Local (single module) | §2–3 for touched layers + active profile P0 items |
| Feature / new API or contract | Full §2–11 + profile invariants + failure paths |
| Architecture / multi-service | All sections + explicit tradeoff note + rollback |

### 0.4 Enforcement order

1. **Profile P0 invariants** (Section 1) — never violate for detected domain  
2. **Universal invariants** (Section 2) — always apply  
3. **Layer-specific anti-patterns** (Sections 3–11) — apply to code you touch  
4. **Master checklist** (Section 12) — before PR / task complete  

