## 1. DYNAMIC SPECIALIZATION ENGINE (CONTEXT-AWARE PRIORITIZATION)

### 1.1 Profile activation rules

- **Multiple profiles** may apply (e.g., B2B SaaS + AI agent + Event-driven).
- When profiles **conflict**, prefer the **higher-severity** invariant (safety > money > privacy > availability > speed).
- **LMP / microservice layout:** When `services/<name>/` exists, also enforce layered `routes → logic → clients` and no cross-service imports regardless of profile.

### 1.2 Detection confidence

| Confidence | Action |
|---|---|
| **High** (deps + paths + domain terms in code/docs) | Enforce profile P0 strictly; cite profile in review |
| **Medium** (partial signals) | Apply profile P0 for touched code paths; flag assumption |
| **Low** (guess only) | Default to PROFILE Z; ask user only if violation would be irreversible (payments, PHI, prod delete) |

---

### PROFILE A — Fintech, Payments & Ledgers

**Detect when:** Wallets, ledgers, checkout, refunds, Stripe/Adyen/Plaid, double-entry, settlement, FX, invoicing, balance APIs.

| Priority | Invariant (testable) |
|---|---|
| P0 | **Conservation:** No money created or destroyed in a transaction chain |
| P0 | **Idempotency:** Retries never double-charge or double-credit |
| P0 | **Audit immutability:** Financial facts append-only; corrections via offset entries |

**Critical anti-patterns:**

- Read-modify-write balances without locking, OCC version field, or atomic `UPDATE balance = balance - ?`
- Missing client `idempotency_key` with DB/cache unique constraint on `(key, scope)`
- `float` / `double` for currency — use integer minor units or `Decimal`
- Multi-account writes without single ACID transaction or compensating saga + reconciliation job
- Treating payment webhooks as authoritative without signature verification and replay protection

---

### PROFILE B — Healthcare, PHI & Clinical Systems

**Detect when:** EHR, FHIR, HL7, PHI/PII fields, diagnoses, prescriptions, imaging, lab results, HIPAA references.

| Priority | Invariant |
|---|---|
| P0 | **Confidentiality:** PHI encrypted in transit/rest; masked in logs and non-clinical UIs |
| P0 | **Fail-safe:** Clinical/API failure → human review or protocol fallback — never silent wrong defaults |
| P0 | **Audit:** Clinical actions non-repudiable (who, when, what, why) |

**Critical anti-patterns:**

- Logging request bodies, URLs, or errors containing patient identifiers or clinical narrative
- Sequential integer patient IDs without tenant/clinic authorization on every read path (IDOR)
- Substituting placeholder clinical values when upstream APIs fail
- Unencrypted service-to-service PHI on internal networks (“trusted VPC” fallacy)

---

### PROFILE C — AI / ML & Agentic Systems

**Detect when:** LLM SDKs, RAG, embeddings, tool-calling agents, prompt templates, guardrails, eval harnesses.

| Priority | Invariant |
|---|---|
| P0 | **Deterministic gates:** Model output cannot directly execute irreversible mutations |
| P0 | **Bounded execution:** Hard caps on loops, tokens, cost, wall-clock per request |
| P0 | **Ground-truth separation:** Generated text ≠ verified facts in downstream logic |

**Critical anti-patterns:**

- Unbounded agent loops or recursive tool calls without `max_iterations` and budget ceiling
- User input interpolated into system prompts without isolation (tags, structured I/O, schema validation)
- Writing raw model outputs into RAG index / training feedback without human or rule filter
- Blocking HTTP handlers on synchronous LLM calls for user-facing latency-sensitive routes
- No eval regression set before prompt or model changes

---

### PROFILE D — B2B SaaS & Multi-Tenant

**Detect when:** `tenant_id`, organizations, workspaces, RBAC, per-tenant config, row-level security.

| Priority | Invariant |
|---|---|
| P0 | **Isolation:** Tenant A cannot read/write/list Tenant B data by any path |
| P0 | **Fairness:** One tenant cannot exhaust shared pools (connections, CPU, rate limits) |
| P0 | **Capability-based auth:** Permissions are capabilities, not role name string compares |

**Critical anti-patterns:**

- Queries without `tenant_id` (or DB RLS) on shared tables
- Cache keys without tenant prefix (`user:42` vs `tenant:9:user:42`)
- `if role == "Admin"` instead of `can("resource:action")`
- Global rate limits only — no per-tenant quotas on expensive endpoints

---

### PROFILE E — Event-Driven & Streaming

**Detect when:** Kafka, Pub/Sub, SQS, RabbitMQ, Celery, consumers, outbox, sagas, CDC.

| Priority | Invariant |
|---|---|
| P0 | **At-least-once + idempotent consumers** |
| P0 | **Poison isolation:** Bad messages must not stall the partition |
| P0 | **Ordering:** Per-aggregate sequence preserved where state depends on order |

**Critical anti-patterns:**

- Uncaught handler exceptions killing the consumer without DLQ
- Assuming exactly-once delivery from the broker
- Parallel workers processing `Paid` before `Created` for same `order_id`
- Unbounded in-memory batch buffers in workers

---

### PROFILE F — E-Commerce, Inventory & Marketplaces

**Detect when:** Carts, orders, SKUs, inventory reservation, shipping, promotions, sellers/buyers.

| Priority | Invariant |
|---|---|
| P0 | **Inventory:** Reserved ≤ available (unless explicit oversell policy) |
| P0 | **Order state machine:** Valid transitions only; no skipped states |
| P0 | **Price at checkout:** Price locked at commit time, not display time |

**Critical anti-patterns:**

- Check-then-act inventory without reservation TTL or row lock
- Double application of discounts on retry
- Lost updates on concurrent cart merges

---

### PROFILE G — IoT, Edge & Cyber-Physical

**Detect when:** Device telemetry, MQTT, firmware OTA, sensors, actuators, time-series at scale.

| Priority | Invariant |
|---|---|
| P0 | **Safety interlocks** cannot be bypassed without logged override |
| P0 | **Command authenticity** on device control paths |
| P0 | **Backpressure** on ingest when processing lags |

**Critical anti-patterns:**

- Actuating devices from unauthenticated or unsigned commands
- Blocking hot path on synchronous cloud round-trip
- No clock skew / ordering strategy for telemetry

---

### PROFILE H — Government, Legal & High-Audit

**Detect when:** Immutable audit logs, retention policies, approvals, FOIA, classification labels.

| Priority | Invariant |
|---|---|
| P0 | **Tamper-evident audit trail** for privileged actions |
| P0 | **Retention / deletion** rules enforced in code, not wiki |
| P0 | **Separation of duties** on sensitive operations |

**Critical anti-patterns:**

- Overwriting audit rows; soft-delete without retention metadata
- Single actor can submit and approve same high-risk action
- Undocumented admin bypass endpoints

---

### PROFILE I — Real-Time & Collaborative

**Detect when:** WebSockets, SSE, CRDT, presence, live cursors, shared documents.

| Priority | Invariant |
|---|---|
| P0 | **Auth on every channel join** |
| P0 | **Conflict strategy explicit** (LWW, OT, CRDT) |
| P0 | **Reconnect** with state sync and jitter |

**Critical anti-patterns:**

- Broadcasting events before authorization check
- Unbounded fan-out on single write
- No heartbeat / stale connection cleanup

---

### PROFILE J — Analytics, ETL & Data Warehouse

**Detect when:** dbt, Airflow, Spark, batch pipelines, BI exports, CDC to warehouse.

| Priority | Invariant |
|---|---|
| P0 | **Lineage:** Source → transform → sink traceable |
| P0 | **Idempotent batch runs** (safe replays) |
| P0 | **PII handling** in exports (masking, aggregation thresholds) |

**Critical anti-patterns:**

- Full-table scans in prod OLTP for analytics
- Non-deterministic transforms breaking replay
- Joining production PII into dev environments

---

### PROFILE Z — General Application (default)

**Use when:** No specific profile triggers, or greenfield with unknown domain.

| Priority | Invariant |
|---|---|
| P0 | **Correctness** over speed for mutations |
| P0 | **Explicit contracts** at system boundaries |
| P0 | **Fail loud in dev, fail safe for users in prod** |

Apply all of **Sections 2–12** without domain-specific elevation.

