## 2. UNIVERSAL INVARIANTS (ALWAYS APPLY)

State these as **testable claims** for non-trivial work:

| # | Invariant | Violation symptom |
|---|---|---|
| U1 | Inputs validated at boundary before trust | Injection, corruption, crashes |
| U2 | Secrets never in source, logs, or client payloads | Breach, compliance failure |
| U3 | External calls have timeout + bounded retry | Hung threads, cascades |
| U4 | Errors are structured and safe for clients | Fragile clients, info leak |
| U5 | List endpoints bounded (pagination/cursor) | OOM, timeouts |
| U6 | Mutations idempotent or explicitly deduped | Duplicate records on retry |
| U7 | Observability: correlation ID across hops | Un-debuggable production |
| U8 | Tests assert behavior, not mock choreography | False confidence |
| U9 | No silent `except` — failures visible | Hidden corruption |
| U10 | Configuration single-sourced (`settings` / env — see `no-hardcoded-env-vars`) | Env drift, secret leak |

