## 3. ARCHITECTURAL ANTI-PATTERNS (DOMAIN-AGNOSTIC)

### 3.1 Tight coupling & boundary violations

- **Mistake:** Importing another service’s modules, ORM models, or DB helpers across deployable boundaries.
- **Why:** Coordinated deploys, ripple breakage, hidden contracts.
- **Rule:** Black-box services. Integrate via versioned APIs, events, or SDK generated from OpenAPI/Proto — never shared internal code paths.

### 3.2 God module / monolith-in-disguise

- **Mistake:** One deployable owns unrelated domains; files >>400 lines of mixed concerns.
- **Why:** Cannot scale, test, or own independently.
- **Rule:** One bounded context per service/module. Split by **change reason**, not technical layer alone.

### 3.3 Distributed monolith

- **Mistake:** Shared database tables across services; mandatory sync chain of 3+ calls per user action; deploy-all-together releases.
- **Why:** Microservice ops cost without isolation benefit.
- **Rule:** Database-per-service (logical or physical). Long workflows → async jobs, sagas, outbox — not blocking chains.

### 3.4 Chatty integration

- **Mistake:** N+1 HTTP/RPC calls to assemble one response.
- **Why:** Latency multiplies; failure combinations explode.
- **Rule:** Batch APIs, materialized read models, BFF aggregation, or denormalized cache — measure p99 call fan-out.

### 3.5 Missing API versioning

- **Mistake:** Breaking JSON shapes on live URLs.
- **Why:** Mobile and partner clients break on deploy.
- **Rule:** Version prefix (`/v1/`). Breaking → new version; deprecate with timeline.

### 3.6 Shared mutable process state

- **Mistake:** Module-level dicts/lists mutated per request; singleton caches without TTL.
- **Why:** Race conditions; horizontal scale breaks; memory leaks.
- **Rule:** Request-scoped state only. Shared cache → external store with TTL and namespacing.

### 3.7 Leaky abstractions upward

- **Mistake:** DB schema, queue names, vendor SDK types leak into HTTP responses or UI models.
- **Why:** Refactors become impossible; security exposure.
- **Rule:** Map at boundaries (DTO / Pydantic response models / view models).

---

## 4. CODE-LEVEL ANTI-PATTERNS (DOMAIN-AGNOSTIC)

### 4.1 Fat transport layer (routes/controllers/handlers)

- **Mistake:** SQL, business rules, third-party calls inside HTTP handlers.
- **Why:** Untestable; framework lock-in; cannot reuse from CLI/workers.
- **Rule:** Transport parses auth + input, delegates to **logic/service layer**, maps output. *(LMP: `routes.py` → `logic.py`.)*

### 4.2 Fat models vs anemic everything

- **Mistake:** ORM/Pydantic models that call networks; or zero validation on DTOs.
- **Why:** Cycles, duplicated validation, runtime surprises.
- **Rule:** Models validate shape; orchestration in logic layer; domain rules as validators or domain services.

### 4.3 Untyped internals (`dict`, `any`, `interface{}`)

- **Mistake:** Passing loose JSON maps through layers.
- **Why:** KeyError at runtime; refactors fail silently.
- **Rule:** Typed schemas at every boundary; static analysis enabled (`mypy`, `tsc`, etc.).

### 4.4 Copy-paste divergence

- **Mistake:** Same 5+ lines in two places with drift.
- **Rule:** Extract once; parameterize differences.

### 4.5 Broad exception swallowing

- **Mistake:** `except Exception: pass` or generic catch returning 200.
- **Rule:** Catch specific types; log traceback + context; map to safe client errors.

### 4.6 Missing type hints / null discipline

- **Mistake:** Untyped public functions; nullable fields unchecked.
- **Rule:** Types on all public APIs; explicit optional handling.

### 4.7 Sync-over-async / blocking the event loop

- **Mistake:** Sync I/O or CPU work inside async handlers.
- **Rule:** Async clients; offload blocking via thread pool / worker queue.

### 4.8 Hardcoded configuration

- **Mistake:** URLs, keys, limits in source.
- **Rule:** See `no-hardcoded-env-vars` — `settings` singleton only.

---

## 5. DATA & STATE ANTI-PATTERNS (DOMAIN-AGNOSTIC)

### 5.1 N+1 queries

- Loop + query per row. **Fix:** JOIN, `IN (...)`, DataLoader, batch RPC.

### 5.2 Missing indexes

- Filter/sort on unindexed columns at scale. **Fix:** Index review with EXPLAIN for each new hot path.

### 5.3 Large blobs in OLTP

- PDF/HTML/images in row storage. **Fix:** Object storage + pointer metadata.

### 5.4 Ignoring replication lag

- Read replica immediately after write. **Fix:** Read-your-writes routing or tolerate staleness in UX.

### 5.5 Lost updates & race conditions

- Last-write-wins without version column. **Fix:** Optimistic locking, compare-and-swap, or serializable isolation where needed.

### 5.6 Unbounded transactions

- Long locks holding user-facing requests. **Fix:** Short transactions; saga for multi-step.

### 5.7 Schema drift without migration discipline

- Manual prod DDL. **Fix:** Versioned migrations; backward-compatible expand-contract.

---

## 6. API & CONTRACT ANTI-PATTERNS (DOMAIN-AGNOSTIC)

### 6.1 Inconsistent error shapes

- Mix of `error`, `message`, `detail`, plain text, stack traces.
- **Rule:** One schema, e.g. `{"detail": string, "errorCode": string}` (+ optional `fieldErrors` for validation).

### 6.2 Non-idempotent POST

- Retries create duplicates. **Fix:** Idempotency-Key header + unique constraint.

### 6.3 Unpaginated collections

- **Rule:** Default `limit` ≤ 100; max cap enforced; cursor preferred for live feeds.

### 6.4 Leaking internals

- Stack traces, SQL, internal IDs in JSON. **Fix:** Map to public DTOs; generic 500 message.

### 6.5 Sync long-running work

- User waits >5–10s on HTTP. **Fix:** `202` + `jobId` + poll/webhook; progress events.

### 6.6 Weak input validation

- Trust URL, path, HTML, regex from client. **Fix:** Allowlists, max lengths, canonicalization, SSRF checks (§8.2).

### 6.7 Ambiguous HTTP semantics

- GET with side effects; DELETE returning body without contract.
- **Rule:** REST verbs match semantics; document exceptions.

### 6.8 Missing contract tests

- Hand-written clients drift from server. **Fix:** OpenAPI/Proto as source of truth; CI contract diff.

---

## 7. PERFORMANCE & SCALABILITY (DOMAIN-AGNOSTIC)

### 7.1 No caching plan

- Repeat identical reads. **Fix:** TTL cache; invalidate on write; stampede protection.

### 7.2 Unbounded concurrency

- `gather` thousands of tasks. **Fix:** Semaphores, bulkheads, queue depth limits.

### 7.3 No timeouts

- **Rule:** Connect + read timeouts on every outbound call; DB statement timeouts.

### 7.4 Connection churn

- New TCP/DB per request. **Fix:** Pools in lifespan/startup.

### 7.5 Memory blowups

- Load full file/result set. **Fix:** Streaming, pagination, generators.

### 7.6 Hot keys & skew

- Single shard or cache key for global counter. **Fix:** Shard keys, approximate aggregates, local increments + flush.

### 7.7 Missing backpressure

- Producer outruns consumer. **Fix:** Rate limit ingest; pause acknowledgments; scale consumers with lag metric.

---

## 8. RELIABILITY & RESILIENCE (DOMAIN-AGNOSTIC)

### 8.1 Retry storm (no jitter)

- **Fix:** Exponential backoff + full jitter; max attempts; retry only idempotent ops.

### 8.2 No circuit breaker

- Hammer dead dependency. **Fix:** Open circuit after failure threshold; half-open probe.

### 8.3 No health endpoints

- **Fix:** Lightweight `GET /health` (liveness); `GET /ready` optional (deps, without heavy queries).

### 8.4 No graceful shutdown

- SIGKILL mid-write. **Fix:** Drain connections; stop accepting; flush outbox; SIGTERM handler.

### 8.5 Single point of failure

- One region, one broker, one admin. **Fix:** Document RTO/RPO; multi-AZ; rehearse failover.

### 8.6 Missing bulkheads

- One slow tenant blocks all. **Fix:** Per-tenant pools and timeouts.

### 8.7 No reconciliation

- Partial saga success. **Fix:** Scheduled reconcile jobs; alerts on drift.

---

## 9. SECURITY (DOMAIN-AGNOSTIC)

### 9.1 Injection (SQL, NoSQL, Cypher, LDAP, command)

- String concat with user input. **Fix:** Parameterized queries; ORM; input typing.

### 9.2 SSRF

- Server fetches user URL. **Fix:** Allowlist hosts; block private/link-local/metadata IPs; no redirects to internal.

### 9.3 Broken access control (IDOR, privilege escalation)

- **Fix:** Authorize every object access; default deny; test horizontal + vertical escalation.

### 9.4 Secrets in repo/logs

- **Fix:** Secret manager; pre-commit secret scan; log redaction.

### 9.5 Overly permissive CORS / CSP gaps

- `*` origins in prod. **Fix:** Explicit origin list per environment.

### 9.6 Missing rate limiting & abuse controls

- **Fix:** Global + per-identity limits; cost-based throttling on expensive endpoints.

### 9.7 Insufficient auth session hygiene

- Long-lived tokens without rotation; missing revocation on role change.

### 9.8 Supply chain risk

- Unpinned deps; unverified packages. **Fix:** Lockfiles; SBOM; vulnerability CI gate.

### 9.9 Prompt / tool injection (when AI present)

- Tools callable with user-controlled args without schema validation. **Fix:** Allowlisted tools; human gate on destructive tools.

---

## 10. OBSERVABILITY (DOMAIN-AGNOSTIC)

### 10.1 Unstructured logs / print debugging

- **Fix:** JSON logs; severity; stable field names.

### 10.2 Missing correlation ID

- **Fix:** Generate/propagate `requestId` / `traceparent` on ingress; inject in logs and outbound headers.

### 10.3 Logging secrets & PII

- **Fix:** Allowlist fields; centralized scrubber; sampling for high-cardinality debug.

### 10.4 Metrics without SLOs

- **Fix:** RED/USE metrics; alert on user-visible symptoms (error rate, p95 latency), not only CPU.

### 10.5 No tracing on distributed paths

- **Fix:** OpenTelemetry on inbound + outbound HTTP and DB.

---

## 11. TESTING (DOMAIN-AGNOSTIC)

### 11.1 No tests on core logic

- **Fix:** Unit tests on pure logic; >80% coverage target on critical paths (per TDD rule).

### 11.2 Testing mocks instead of behavior

- Asserting `mock.assert_called`. **Fix:** Assert outputs, DB state, HTTP status, side effects.

### 11.3 Flaky time/order/network tests

- **Fix:** Freeze time; deterministic fixtures; hermetic unit layer.

### 11.4 Unit tests hitting real external systems

- **Fix:** Mock at `clients/` / adapter boundary; integration in dedicated env only.

### 11.5 Missing failure-path tests

- Timeouts, 409 conflicts, validation errors, partial saga — not only happy path.

### 11.6 No load / soak for scale-critical features

- **Fix:** Load test before claiming 10× readiness.

---

## 12. DEPLOYMENT, INFRA & WORKFLOW (DOMAIN-AGNOSTIC)

### 12.1 Environment drift

- Different deps/config shapes per env. **Fix:** Same image; config via env; parity checklist.

### 12.2 Unpinned dependencies

- Floating ranges in prod. **Fix:** Exact pins; automated update PRs with CI.

### 12.3 Inefficient container builds

- `COPY .` before dep install. **Fix:** Layer cache: deps first, code last; slim base.

### 12.4 Missing probes

- **Fix:** Startup + liveness wired to real `/health`.

### 12.5 Giant PRs & rubber-stamp review

- **Fix:** ~300 LOC target; one concern per PR; reviewers use this rule as checklist.

### 12.6 Skipping design brief on non-trivial work

- **Fix:** ETB in `project.md` + approval before code (per user workflow rules).

### 12.7 No rollback plan

- **Fix:** Feature flags; backward-compatible migrations; documented revert steps.

